Simple install procedure
========================

  % gzip -cd tsar-2.1.0.tar.gz | tar xvf -  # unpack the sources
  % cd tsar-2.1.0                           # change to the toplevel directory
  % ./configure                             # run the `configure' script
  % make                                    # build tsar

  [ Become root if necessary ]
  % make install                            # install tsar tsar-devel
  % make uninstall                          # uninstall tsar tsar-devel

RPM install 
========================

  %gzip -cd tsar-2.1.0.tar.gz | tar xvf -  # unpack the sources
  %cd tsar-2.1.0/rpm                       # change to the rpm directory
  %sh tsar-build.sh .. tsar 2.1.0 1        # create rpm for tsar tsar-devel
  %rpm -ivh *.rpm                          # install tsar tsar-devel by rpm

